{"source_key":"sha256-0edd3617078ce3ae5018a0bc330f7fea","record_index":334,"record_hash":"sha256:af2ccec6cfd83a4aa4ec5dfae7c8ebb1462fc4b79af790491da66e371a7eb781","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:05:09.489Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 2d53d2\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2267\nOutput:\n     1\t# Agent Trail\n     2\t\n     3\tAgent Trail is the review-adjacent product surface for captured agent sessions.\n     4\tIt is the page a reviewer opens from a pull request to understand the agent work\n     5\tbehind a change.\n     6\t\n     7\t## Working Name\n     8\t\n     9\tUse **Agent Trail** for now.\n    10\t\n    11\tGood PR link text:\n    12\t\n    13\t- View Agent Trail\n    14\t- Explore Agent Trail\n    15\t- Agent Trail for this PR\n    16\t\n    17\tAvoid names like \"transcript\", \"audit log\", or \"provenance report\" for the\n    18\tproduct surface. The page may contain transcript records and provenance facts,\n    19\tbut the user-facing promise is simpler: follow the useful trail behind this\n    20\tchange.\n    21\t\n    22\t## Product Shape\n    23\t\n    24\tFor v1, a reviewer starts from a GitHub pull request URL and opens the matching\n    25\tGitButler-owned Agent Trail URL by replacing the host. The server builds or\n    26\tloads a generated snapshot for that public pull request.\n    27\t\n    28\tExplicit PR description links, bot comments, check-run details links, or GitHub\n    29\tapp panels can come later as distribution channels. They are not required for\n    30\tthe first build.\n    31\t\n    32\tThe page lets the reviewer explore captured agent context related to the pull\n    33\trequest:\n    34\t\n    35\t- prompts and requests from the human\n    36\t- assistant responses and claims\n    37\t- tool calls and tool results\n    38\t- tests and validation attempts\n    39\t- decisions and tradeoffs\n    